<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-07-0112 </DOCNO><TEXT>Today, people think of nuclear fission in terms of its applications toenergy production or to manufacture of nuclear arms. Fifty years ago,however, and in the ensuing few years, fission was a new, unexpectedphenomenonwhich excited physicists all over the world. This article givesa personal recollection of those years as seen through the eyes of amember of the Niels Bohr Institute in Copenhagen. 5 refs., 2 figs.</TEXT></DOC>